• What is meant by polymorphism ?

  Polymorphism is the ability of any data to be processed in more than one form
  Its also a property through which any message can be sent to objects of multiple classes, 
  and every object has the tendency to respond in an appropriate way depending on the class properties.

• How does polymorphism work in the above program?

  An animals at the same time can have different roles to play in life. Like a cat at the name is Kurre, Basme, and others. while dog is  
  So the same animals has to have many features but has to implement each as per the situation and the condition.
  
